And you can read all about that in the Blastula help site. And then on the R Markdown side, you have to attach the subject line here.

00:42:46.040 --> 00:42:50.040
So this is the subject line. This is the body. These are images and these are attachments.

00:42:50.040 --> 00:42:55.040
So the XLS file gets attached here in the R Markdown file. Makes sense.

00:42:55.040 --> 00:42:58.040
So what that's going to this is all the email.

00:42:58.040 --> 00:43:04.040
Now, I also make the XLS file here available as a link to the report.

00:43:04.040 --> 00:43:10.040
And this is an RStudio Connect feature, but because I can make that work really nicely.

00:43:10.040 --> 00:43:14.040
But this is I think what you're looking for.

00:43:14.040 --> 00:43:28.040
I wanted to just briefly mention, since I didn't take out the PowerPoint thing, I just want to make sure that you're aware that when we do like a presentation here on R Markdown,

00:43:28.040 --> 00:43:33.040
if you come here to presentation on R Markdown, one of the options is PowerPoint.

00:43:33.040 --> 00:43:47.040
So you can actually generate PowerPoints here. And then in PowerPoint, going back to the web shots, you can put web shots in here to like, you know, pick up the things that you're trying to insert into the PowerPoint.

