00:49:04.040 --> 00:49:07.040
You're like, hi, it's not even SQL, but they put HQL on top of it.

00:49:07.040 --> 00:49:14.040
So I think SQL is one of the most enduring paradigms in technology that I'm aware of.

00:49:14.040 --> 00:49:17.040
And don't bet against it.

00:49:17.040 --> 00:49:19.040
I think it's great.

00:49:19.040 --> 00:49:21.040
I think everyone should.

00:49:21.040 --> 00:49:24.040
SQL is just a skill that's great to have.

00:49:24.040 --> 00:49:27.040
I don't want to riff too long on this because I could go on,

00:49:27.040 --> 00:49:33.040
but I think one of the problems with SQL in general, with the world,

00:49:33.040 --> 00:49:37.040
is very few people get formalized SQL training.

00:49:37.040 --> 00:49:39.040
I was lucky enough to get that.

00:49:39.040 --> 00:49:42.040
So I learned SQL on the job.

00:49:42.040 --> 00:49:45.040
Nobody in academia talks about SQL, right?

00:49:45.040 --> 00:49:49.040
I shouldn't say nobody, but nobody in my experience in academia ever mentions anything about SQL.

00:49:49.040 --> 00:49:52.040
And then I go into the job and that's all anybody was doing.

00:49:52.040 --> 00:49:54.040
So I learned SQL that way.

00:49:54.040 --> 00:49:56.040
But then I actually did take a training class on SQL

00:49:56.040 --> 00:49:58.040
and then talked about the query planners, right,

00:49:58.040 --> 00:50:03.040
and other clauses that maybe you're not so familiar with.

00:50:03.040 --> 00:50:06.040
And window functions and different styles of it.

00:50:06.040 --> 00:50:07.040
And that was very useful.

00:50:07.040 --> 00:50:12.040
So if you really wanted to do something hardcore, you can get formalized training.

00:50:12.040 --> 00:50:14.040
I don't think it's necessary,

00:50:14.040 --> 00:50:18.040
but if it makes you feel like more of an expert or feel better about your skills,

00:50:18.040 --> 00:50:23.040
those things are out there.

