00:57:03.040 --> 00:57:06.040
You can win those arguments because it makes sense, right?

00:57:06.040 --> 00:57:09.040
It's, like, you take the emotion of the people out of it.

00:57:09.040 --> 00:57:12.040
You can say, like, hey, we need this thing, right?

00:57:12.040 --> 00:57:15.040
And, you know, organizations will struggle a little bit because they don't –

00:57:15.040 --> 00:57:17.040
a lot of them don't get data science.

00:57:17.040 --> 00:57:19.040
We don't understand what you guys are doing, right?

00:57:19.040 --> 00:57:20.040
But that's changing.

00:57:20.040 --> 00:57:21.040
That's all changing, right?

00:57:21.040 --> 00:57:29.040
Like, that's, you know, AI algorithm or, like, common vernacular now in the world.

00:57:29.040 --> 00:57:33.040
Like, you know, my grandma's passed on, but if I had a grandma still,

00:57:33.040 --> 00:57:37.040
she would know what AI was, and she would be pretty ticked off about algorithms

00:57:37.040 --> 00:57:39.040
for some reason.

00:57:39.040 --> 00:57:42.040
And data science is mainstream now.

00:57:42.040 --> 00:57:45.040
Most of them are not data-driven at all.

00:57:45.040 --> 00:57:48.040
And for them, it's one extra step that they need to do.

00:57:48.040 --> 00:57:49.040
And, you know, like, people are lazy.

00:57:49.040 --> 00:57:54.040
They don't really want to do an extra step if they can, like –

00:57:54.040 --> 00:57:56.040
if they don't have to.

00:57:56.040 --> 00:58:01.040
So before they realize all the benefits, they need to do effort.

00:58:01.040 --> 00:58:02.040
Yeah, yeah.

00:58:02.040 --> 00:58:08.040
There's usually some sort of fulcrum, and getting that executive sponsor is key.

00:58:08.040 --> 00:58:12.040
Like, if there's no executive sponsor, no one's willing to actually say,

00:58:12.040 --> 00:58:15.040
yes, this is what we're going to do, then you really – you're back in that –

00:58:15.040 --> 00:58:18.040
you're back in the guerrilla warfare, right?

00:58:18.040 --> 00:58:21.040
